What are Self-driving Cars?
Self-driving cars, also known as autonomous vehicles (AVs), represent the pinnacle of automotive innovation, capable of sensing their environment and operating without human intervention. These vehicles utilize a sophisticated combination of sensors, cameras, radar, lidar, and artificial intelligence to navigate roads, detect obstacles, and make real-time driving decisions. The technology spans six levels of automation (0-5) as defined by SAE International, with current commercial applications primarily focusing on Levels 2-4 automation. The potential to revolutionize transportation extends beyond personal vehicles to encompass ride-hailing services, freight transport, and public mobility solutions, fundamentally transforming how people and goods move through our cities and highways.
